==English==
===Homophones===
*[[ferment]]
===Etymology===
From {{L.}} [[fomentare]] "to promote"
===Verb===
{{en-infl-reg-consonant|foment||}}
#To nurse to life or activity; to cherish and promote by excitements; to encourage; to abet; to instigate; &mdash; used often in a pejorative sense; as, to foment ill humors.
#To apply a warm lotion to; to bathe with a cloth or sponge wet with warm water or medicated liquid.
#To cherish with heat; to foster.